	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=32254"><span id=" ">Nixoh</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">484 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Decent [2.77]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Couple of things: 1) INT isn't linear, you get different amounts of mana for each point of INT depending on what your INT is. 2) There's a (recently increased) mana cap from items.<br/><br/>INT from mana is kind of ignorable. If you're an INT caster, you should max your INT, period. Once you do, you should focus on getting that INT down to as few slots as possible so that you can get items that you need for other reasons (e.g. focus, mana, HP, etc) in other slots.<br/><br/>That said, this is a very nice earring, and yes the resists are very nice. I'm going to be turning it down ;-)<br/></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />You gain experience!<br/>The Goblin Warlord hits YOU for 50 points!<br/></td></tr>
